Examples how to use Pythia8:

1) main01 - main07 are strictly internal to Pythia8
* main01.cc : brief example with charged multiplicity distribution
* main02.cc : brief example with Z0 pT spectrum
* main03.cc & main03.cmnd : simple single-particle analysis in jet events
* main04.cc & main04.cmnd : simple tests of event properties
* main05.cc : cone-jet analysis of LHC events
* main06.cc & main06.cmnd : study elastic/diffractive events
* main07.cc & main07.cmnd : study minimum-bias events
* main08.cc : combine results of subruns in separate pT bins

2) main11 - main18 link to Pythia6 or other files that come along
* main11.cc & main11.cmnd : extensive tests and event properties 
* main12.cc & main12.cmnd : compare Pythia8 vs. Pythia6 cross sections
* main13.cc : LEP events with sphericity/thrust/jetfinder analysis
+ main14for.f (Fortran!) : have Pythia6 generate a Les Houches Event File 
* main14.cc & ttbar.lhe : generate events from a Les Houches Event File 
* main15.cc & main15.cmnd: & main15.spc supersymmetry production using SLHA
* main16.cc : Les Houches Accord tricked to study fixed parton configurations
* main17.cc: how to link an external decay handler
* main18.cc: how to link an external random number generator

3) main21 requires linkage to HepMC, external to this program package
* main21.cc & main21.cmnd: output to HepMC event record format

Type "gmake mainNN" (or "gmake main14for") to build an executable.
Type "./mainNN.exe > outputfile" to run program. 
Type "gmake clean" to clean up the examples directory (but not output files).

Files outNN are examples of possible output from the respective run.
(Not available for main21, which only works if you linked HepMC properly.)
